title: "Prepare Bank Transfer" is missing an output and an output set
body:
As the source of the Data Association to the Data Store, the "Prepare Bank Transfer" task is missing a dataOutput and outputSet to serve as the sourceRef of the dataOutputAssociation

      <dataOutputAssociation id="DataOutputAssociation_1">
        <targetRef>DataStoreReference_1</targetRef>
      </dataOutputAssociation>

Should be:

			<semantic:ioSpecification>
				<semantic:dataOutput id="_b6adf6f5-dda2-4147-9f24-00d2891f41c4"/>
				<semantic:inputSet/>
				<semantic:outputSet>
					<semantic:dataOutputRefs>_b6adf6f5-dda2-4147-9f24-00d2891f41c4</semantic:dataOutputRefs>
				</semantic:outputSet>
			</semantic:ioSpecification>
			<semantic:dataOutputAssociation id="DataOutputAssociation_1">
				<semantic:sourceRef>_b6adf6f5-dda2-4147-9f24-00d2891f41c4</semantic:sourceRef>
				<semantic:targetRef>DataStoreReference_1</semantic:targetRef>
			</semantic:dataOutputAssociation>

title: BPMNEdge's target redefined for DataOutputAssociation_1
body:
<bpmndi:BPMNEdge id="BPMNEdge_DataOutputAssociation_1" bpmnElement="DataOutputAssociation_1" sourceElement="prepareBankTransfer_gui" targetElement="DataStoreReference_1_gui">
        <omgdi:waypoint xsi:type="omgdc:Point" x="674.0" y="735.0"/>
        <omgdi:waypoint xsi:type="omgdc:Point" x="639.0" y="784.0"/>
      </bpmndi:BPMNEdge>


BPMNEdge's target should be redefined only if it is different from the one of the referred bpmnElement.

See P375 of the spec:
 + targetElement : DiagramElement [0..1] {redefines target}
an optional reference to the edges target element if it is different from the target inferred from the bpmnElement
association.

title: Label of Data Store overlap with the shape according to XML but not in image
body:
The label of the "Financial Accounting System" Data Store overlaps with the shape according to the XML from the reference file below:

    <bpmndi:BPMNShape id="DataStoreReference_1_gui" bpmnElement="DataStoreReference_1">
        <omgdc:Bounds height="60.173" width="62.001" x="587.9995" y="784.9135"/>
        <bpmndi:BPMNLabel>
          <omgdc:Bounds height="22.0" width="176.0" x="530.0" y="843.0"/>
        </bpmndi:BPMNLabel>
      </bpmndi:BPMNShape>

Shape boundaries  on y axis 784+60=844px, So the label (at  y=843) is over the bottom part of the shape in the XML definition.

title: Test Case C.1.0: User Tasks with incoming/outgoing Message Flows
body:
In the process model there is a user task with one outgoing message flow and one outgoing message flow.
I believe this is not conform with the BPMN specification (and in particular, the execution semantics part). The BPMN2 specification says:
"User Task: Upon activation, the User Task is distributed to the assigned person or group of people. When the work has been done, the User Task completes."
Although the BPMN metamodel allows such a constellation - Message Flows can theoretically be connected to any type of Tasks - still the (execution) semantics of incoming and outgoing Message Flows for User Tasks is not defined.
So I would argue that the adopted process model is not a valid BPMN model.
